    "answer": "The most effective approach is to frame the project as a 15-year capital asset, document your current facility's condition with photos, identify what competing programs' facilities look like, and present the recruiting ROI. Including a cost-per-year breakdown (total project cost ÷ 15 years) makes the investment feel manageable. Our team provides budget documentation packages to support approval processes."
